text: The National Party of Australia - NSW, also called the NSW Nationals, is the New South Wales branch of the National Party, a centre-right agrarian party in Australia. It is the junior partner in the Coalition with the Liberal Party, which is currently in Opposition. The current leader of the party is Dugald Saunders and its deputy leader is Bronnie Taylor.
